cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of metro cell antennas on heterogeneous cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses a model of random cell placement based on Poisson distribution and innovative 3D building model that quantifies blockage due to shadowing, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of metro cell antennas on network spectral efficiency and average user throughput, which are related to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the impact of metro cell antennas on network performance without any cooperation or exchange of information between macro cell base stations and metro cells, which is related to social and information networks. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses computational models to demonstrate the impact of metro cell antennas on network performance, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
